SQL Injection

1) SQL injection is a code injection technique that might destroy your database.
2) SQL injection is one of the most common web hacking techniques.
3) SQL Injection is a security vulnerability where an attacker inserts (or â€œinjectsâ€) malicious SQL code into your applicationâ€™s database queries.

How to Avoid SQL Injection

1. Use Prepared Statements (MOST IMPORTANT)
	Example using PDO (recommended) - PHP Data Objects (PDO is a database abstraction layer in PHP.)
	Example using MySQLi

2. Never put user input directly into queries
3. Validate & Sanitize Inputs
4. Use Stored Procedures (Optional)
5. Limit Database Privileges

What is OOPS?

OOPS (Object-Oriented Programming System) is a programming approach where we write code using objects and classes instead of only functions.

Basic OOPS Terms

Class â†’ Blueprint

Object â†’ Real instance of a class 

