6) Encapsulation
Encapsulation means wrapping data (variables) and methods inside a class and restricting direct access using access modifiers. ğŸ‘‰ Example. Public,private,protected.

7) Inheritance
Inheritance allows one class to acquire properties and methods of another class using extends. ğŸ‘‰ Example. Base Model, Base Controller

8) Polymorphism
Polymorphism means same method name but different behavior depending on the object. 

9) Abstraction
Hiding implementation details, showing only essential features or functionality. ğŸ‘‰ Example. Model called inside Controller

